  "text": "Beside the direct relevance for in vivo time-lapse microscopy, our study indicates that our morphological approach to cosegmentation is both practical and of relevance in bioimaging. Consequentially, it appears a natural approach to apply cosegmentation to protein colocalization studies, which have attracted considerable attention in recent years following the availability of two-or multi-label fluorescence microscopy [CITATION_1] .",
